<p>One point to mention is to Note that I BURNT MY LED because the GND pin of my voltage regulator was not connected to the shared ground! The regulator's output pin instead of +5V was giving out +9.8 V ! Just because of a missing GND connection.</p>

<p>I suggest we make the GND connection of our regulator the final gate for all grounds connections in this circuit, so if that goes cut, our circuit would turn off instead of have dangerous voltage !</p>
